title: Print, "Versailles, Gardens, The Pleasures of the Enchanted Isle", 1664
medium: Etching and engraving. Black ink on rolled paper
inscribed:
At center of banner:  "Theatre dresse au milieu du grand Estang representant l'Isle d'Alcine, ou paroissoit son Palais enchante sortant d'un petit rocher dan leque fut  dance un Ballet de plusieurs, entrees, et apres quoy ce Palais fut consume, par un feu d'artifice representant la rupture de l'enchantement apres la fuite de Roger"
At left of banner:  "Troisieme"
At right of banner:  "Journee"
Numbered at lower right: "8"
creditline: Gift of Eleanor and Sarah Hewitt
description: Horizontal rectangle:  In the foreground a banner, and above a frieze of the back of an audience.  At center, a theatre in the middle of the great pond, sea monsters in the pond.  The Palace of Alcina.

tombstone.epitaph:
Print, "Versailles, Gardens, The Pleasures of the Enchanted Isle", 1664.
1664. Etching and engraving. Black ink on rolled paper. Gift of Eleanor and Sarah Hewitt. 1931-86-56.
